sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J64035
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is a variant of the pCASP plasmid with the invB chaperone and sipA secretion signal.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Dan Widmaier
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: These parts come from both genomic and synthetic sources
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This device was designed without biobrick standard assembly in mind so scar sequence restriction sites might exist within the device.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J64009
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The InvB protein is a promiscuous chaperone in the Type III Secretion system (T3S) that assists in the secretion of SipA, SopA, and SopE2 effector proteins. This chaperone binds to the secretion signal of selected proteins and maintains the N-terminus in an unfolded state for secretion by the T3S. The chaperone is critical in coordinating the timing and localization to the proper secretion mechanism and is vital in secreting heterologous proteins with this system.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Dan Widmaier
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This part was not designed to be compatible with biobricks standard assembly

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J64013
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the natural RBS that drives the sipA effector protein in the Salmonella SPI-1 system
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Dan Widmaier
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This part was not designed with compatibility to biobrick standard assembly in mind. This RBS has not been explicitly tested in an expression assasy such as B-Gal or GFP expression.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J64012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the N-terminal 169 amino acids of the SipA effector protein from the Salmonella Type III Secretion System (T3S). These residues comprise the required elements for directing secretion to the T3S. This secretion signal requires the chaperone invB (BBa_J64009) to properly localize to the export apparatus and be secreted in high titer.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Dan Widmaier
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This part was not designed with compatibility to biobrick standard assembly in mind.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J64011
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The natural RBS that drives invB
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Dan Widmaier
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The expression level of this RBS has not been quantified.
